-- Update RSI Strategy with precise example
UPDATE learning_articles SET content = content || E'\n\n## Practice Trade Setup: EUR/USD RSI Example\n\n**Scenario:** EUR/USD daily chart showing RSI oversold bounce\n\n**Setup Details:**\n- **Pair:** EUR/USD\n- **Timeframe:** Daily\n- **Date:** RSI drops to 25 after 5 consecutive red candles\n- **Price at Signal:** 1.0850\n\n**Trade Execution:**\n1. **Entry:** 1.0865 (after RSI crosses back above 30 with bullish candle)\n2. **Stop Loss:** 1.0795 (below recent swing low, 70 pips)\n3. **Take Profit 1:** 1.0935 (1:1 R:R, 70 pips)\n4. **Take Profit 2:** 1.1005 (2:1 R:R, 140 pips)\n\n**Position Sizing Example:**\n- Account: $10,000\n- Risk: 1% = $100\n- Stop: 70 pips = 0.0070\n- Position: $100 / 70 pips = ~$1.43/pip = 0.14 lots\n\n**What to Watch:**\n- RSI divergence at the 30 level (higher lows in RSI while price makes lower lows)\n- Volume spike on the reversal candle\n- Break of short-term trendline confirming reversal'
WHERE slug = 'rsi-trading-strategy';

