-- Update Fibonacci Strategy
UPDATE learning_articles SET content = content || E'\n\n## Practice Trade Setup: S&P 500 Fibonacci Retracement Example\n\n**Scenario:** ES futures pullback to 61.8% Fibonacci level\n\n**Setup Details:**\n- **Instrument:** E-mini S&P 500 (ES)\n- **Timeframe:** Daily\n- **Trend:** Uptrend from 4,100 swing low to 4,400 swing high\n- **Retracement:** Price pulled back to 4,215 (61.8% level)\n\n**Fibonacci Levels:**\n- 0%: 4,400 (swing high)\n- 23.6%: 4,329\n- 38.2%: 4,285\n- 50%: 4,250\n- 61.8%: 4,215 ← Entry Zone\n- 78.6%: 4,164\n- 100%: 4,100 (swing low)\n\n**Trade Execution:**\n1. **Entry:** 4,220 (bullish engulfing at 61.8% with volume)\n2. **Stop Loss:** 4,160 (below 78.6% level, 60 points)\n3. **Take Profit 1:** 4,340 (127.2% extension, 120 points)\n4. **Take Profit 2:** 4,400 (prior high, 180 points)\n\n**Why This Works:**\n- 61.8% is the "golden pocket" - institutional buying zone\n- Confluence with previous support at 4,200\n- Volume spike on reversal candle confirms buyers stepping in'
