-- Update Pairs Trading Strategy  
UPDATE learning_articles SET content = content || E'\n\n## Practice Trade Setup: XOM/CVX Energy Pair\n\n**Scenario:** XOM/CVX ratio diverges 2.5 standard deviations\n\n**Setup Details:**\n- **Long Leg:** Exxon Mobil (XOM) - undervalued\n- **Short Leg:** Chevron (CVX) - overvalued\n- **Correlation:** 0.87 (highly correlated)\n- **Z-Score:** -2.5 (XOM cheap relative to CVX)\n\n**Ratio Analysis:**\n- 60-day Mean Ratio: 1.10 (XOM/CVX)\n- Current Ratio: 0.95 (-2.5 std dev)\n- Target Ratio: 1.10 (mean reversion)\n\n**Trade Execution:**\n1. **Long XOM:** 100 shares at $105.00 = $10,500\n2. **Short CVX:** 65 shares at $160.00 = $10,400\n3. **Dollar Neutral:** ~$100 difference (acceptable)\n\n**Exit Targets:**\n- **Target:** Ratio returns to mean (1.10)\n- **Stop:** Ratio expands to -3.5 std dev\n- **Time Stop:** 30 trading days maximum\n\n**P&L Scenarios:**\n- If ratio returns to 1.10:\n  - XOM rises to $110, CVX flat: +$500 - $0 = +$500\n  - XOM flat, CVX falls to $155: $0 + $325 = +$325\n- Expected: Combination of both moving toward mean\n\n**Risk Management:**\n- Beta-adjusted position if betas differ significantly\n- Monitor correlation daily (exit if < 0.70)\n- Maximum drawdown: 5% of capital allocated'
WHERE slug = 'pairs-trading';

